claim.claim-text:
1. A lightweight cement composition for cementing a subterranean zone penetrated by a well bore comprising: 
a coarse particulate hydraulic cement; 
an ultrafine particulate hydraulic cement mixture comprised of slag cement and a Portland or equivalent cement present in an amount in the range of from about 50% to about 150% by weight of said coarse particulate hydraulic cement in said composition; 
fly ash present in an amount in the range of from about 50% to about 150% by weight of said coarse particulate hydraulic cement in said composition; 
fumed silica present in an amount in the range of from about 20% to about 60% by weight of said coarse particulate hydraulic cement in said composition; 
hollow glass spheres present in an amount sufficient to impart a density to said cement composition in the range of from about 9 to about 13 pounds per gallon; and 
water present in an amount sufficient to form a slurry.
